## 🗺️ Workflow (Step by Step)

```
1. /auth       → Login or Register (no trip form shown yet)
2. /plan       → Trip form (source, dest, dates, time, mode)
3. /api/process → Backend: distance + transport + recommendation engine
4. /dashboard  → Full dashboard with all 13 features
```

## ✅ Features

**Step 1 – Auth**: Login/Register, SQLite storage, hashed passwords, demo accounts

**Step 2 – Plan**: Source/destination, departure/arrival dates, arrival time, Transport Only / Full Trip mode

**Step 3 – Backend**: Haversine distance, transport DB query, CO₂ = distance × carbon_per_km, arrival time check

**Step 4 – Recommendation Engine**: Scores each option on CO₂ (50%) + cost (25%) + duration (25%). Identifies Best Overall 🌟, Greenest 🌱, Cheapest 💰, Fastest ⚡

**Step 5 – Dashboard**: Summary cards, recommendation banner, filterable overview table

**Step 6 – Visual Feedback**: Animated eco tree + CO₂ savings bar per selection

**Step 7 – Charts**: Bar chart, doughnut pie chart, line chart (Chart.js)

**Step 8 – Eco Feedback**: CO₂ saved in kg + tree equivalents, forecast for 1,000 users

**Step 9 – Carbon Forecast**: "If 1,000 users choose this → X kg saved"

**Step 10 – Full Trip Mode**: Eco hotels (with solar/eco badges, images, reviews), Places & Activities, Local Transport options

**Step 11 – Booking**: Simulated confirmation modal + confetti

**Step 12 – User Tracking**: Updates total_co2_saved, eco_score, garden_plants in DB

**Step 13 – Leaderboard**: Top 20 users ranked by CO₂ saved, current user highlighted

## 🗂️ Structure

```
ecovoyage/
├── app.py                  # Flask backend + recommendation engine
├── ecovoyage.db            # Auto-created SQLite database
├── requirements.txt
├── templates/
│   ├── auth.html           # Step 1: Login / Register
│   ├── plan.html           # Step 2: Trip Planning Form
│   └── dashboard.html      # Steps 3–13: Full dashboard
└── static/
    └── css/base.css        # Global design system
```

## 🎨 Design

- **Font**: Cormorant Garamond (display) + Instrument Sans (body)
- **Palette**: Deep forest greens, cream, parchment, amber accents
- **Aesthetic**: Organic Luxury × Editorial
- **Animations**: CSS-only ambient orbs, floating particles, garden growth
